Abakaliki – Ebonyi State Governor, Engr. David Umahi, has congratulated his Rivers State counterpart, Barr Nyesom Wike, on his re-election as the Governor of Rivers State as  declared on Wednesday  by the Independent National Electoral  Commission (INEC). Governor Umahi who is also the Chairman of the South- East Governors Forum in a statement on Thursday in Abakaliki  described the declaration of Wike as the winner of the March 9th Governorship election in Rivers state by INEC ” as a victory for democracy and a pointer to a better democratic norms in the country”. Governor Umahi in the statement which was signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Emmanuel Uzor, extolled Wike’s dogged spirit in protecting the mandate of the people of the state which they overwhelmingly gave to him through their votes. Umahi commended the INEC for standing firm and doing that which is right, adding that there was still hope that Nigeria will still get it better in terms of conducting free and credible elections in future. The Ebonyi Governor called on all the political actors in the state to join hands together with Wike to move the state forward, adding that Nigerians should eschew politics of bitterness and see politics as a vehicle to render selfless services to mankind